            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "Recent funding volatility and proposed cuts have threatened the U.S. space science workforce and the viability of long-term missions. This request addresses the need for funding stability to ensure NASA can execute high-priority missions defined by the National Academies and maintain global leadership against rising international competition, particularly from China.",
            "rationale": "Draws on advocacy talking points regarding workforce stability and international competition.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:reec78c27816a44afa6d43be98eba271e:6b367a706d08",
            "label": "Please describe the goals and/or expected outcome of this Programmatic request:",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "The goal is to provide $9 billion for the Science Mission Directorate to advance American leadership in space. Outcomes include the continued development of transformative missions across planetary science, astrophysics, and heliophysics, while supporting a robust domestic STEM workforce and strengthening the aerospace industrial base.",
            "rationale": "Uses the $9B ask amount and themes of leadership and workforce development.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r4d93a655a9ee470db3fe61e6bc006cc8:3cde68f76e89",
            "label": "Description of this Programmatic request\u0000(500 characters or less):",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "This programmatic request seeks $9,000,000,000 for NASA's Science Mission Directorate. These funds will support critical space exploration missions, ensure the U.S. remains the world leader in scientific discovery, and provide stability for the specialized workforce and industrial base that supports NASA's mission across all 50 states.",
            "rationale": "Concise summary using the required $9B figure and workforce themes.",
            "confidence": "high"
